article.headline: Green Bay 61, W. Michigan 51
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Reserves Bryquis Perine and Ryan Tillema scored 15 points each for Wisconsin-Green Bay, which beat Western Michigan 61-51 Tuesday night. Perine hit six of his first seven shots and all three of his 3-point attempts as the Phoenix (9-4) won their third straight. Shawntes Gary scored 15 points for Western Michigan (3-10), which has lost six of its last seven games. Green Bay's bench outscored the Broncos' reserves 32-11 and outrebounded them 9-4. Western Michigan's David Kool missed 10 of his first 12 shots and finished with 12 points.
